<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Feasibility assessments</title>
    <para> 
        The Rational Unified Process requires that at the end of each phase the feasibility of
        the project has to be re-assessed. In this way the Rational Unified Process tries to ensure
        that investment into doomed projects is limited. 
    </para>
</section>
